.TH "i915_capture_error_state" 9 "i915_capture_error_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i915_capture_error_state \- capture an error record for later analysis
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" i915_capture_error_state
.BI "(struct intel_gt *gt "  ","
.BI "intel_engine_mask_t engine_mask "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "gt" 12
intel_gt which originated the hang
.IP "engine_mask" 12
hung engines
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Should be called when an error is detected (either a hang or an error
interrupt) to capture error state from the time of the error.  Fills
out a structure which becomes available in debugfs for user level tools
to pick up.
